.TH "NAVIGATEEVENT.USERINITIATED" "3JS" "December 9, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
NavigateEvent.userInitiated \- NavigateEvent: userInitiated property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]userInitiated\f[B]\f[R] read\-only property of the
\f[CR]NavigateEvent\f[R] interface returns \f[CR]true\f[R] if the
navigation was initiated by the user (e.g., by clicking a link,
submitting a form, or pressing the browser\(cqs
\(lqBack\(rq/\(lqForward\(rq buttons), or \f[CR]false\f[R] otherwise.
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] The table found at \c
.UR https://github.com/WICG/navigation-api#appendix-types-of-navigations
Appendix: types of navigations
.UE \c
\ shows which navigation types are user\-initiated.
.RE
.SH VALUE
A boolean value\(em\f[CR]true\f[R] if the navigation is user\-initiated,
\f[CR]false\f[R] if not.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Getting \f[CR]userInitiated\f[R] for an event
.IP
.EX
navigation.addEventListener(\(dqnavigate\(dq, (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  console.log(event.userInitiated);
});
.EE
